//! Whisper text decoder — autoregressive transformer with self-attention
//! (causal, growing KV cache) and cross-attention (against frozen encoder K/V).
//!
//! Reference: arXiv 2212.04356 (Whisper — Robust Speech Recognition via
//! Large-Scale Weak Supervision, Radford et al. 2022).
//! https://arxiv.org/abs/2212.04356
//!
//! Architecture (per decode step):
//!   1. Embed token via tied `decoder_token_embed.weight`, add learned
//!      `decoder_pos_embed.weight[pos]`. Whisper uses *learned* positional
//!      embeddings, NOT RoPE — Q/K are not rotated.
//!   2. For each decoder layer (pre-norm everywhere):
//!        a. self-attn  : x = x + self_attn(self_ln(x), causal, growing KV)
//!        b. cross-attn : x = x + cross_attn(cross_ln(x), frozen audio K/V)
//!        c. mlp        : x = x + fc2(gelu(fc1(mlp_ln(x))))
//!   3. ln_final, then logits = x @ decoder_token_embed.weight.T (tied head).
//!
//! Cross-attention K and V are computed once per utterance from the encoder
//! output (call `prepare_audio_context`) and reused for every `decode_step`.
//! Self-attention K and V grow one row per step and live in the per-layer
//! KV cache; call `reset` between utterances.
//!
//! Mirrors `NativeLlamaPipeline::forward_one` for the self-attn / KV cache
//! shape, but swaps RMSNorm→LayerNorm, SwiGLU→GELU, RoPE→learned-pos-embed,
//! and adds the cross-attention block.

use std::sync::Arc;

use crate::loader::WeightBackend;
use crate::math::{gelu_inplace, layer_norm, mat_vec_f32, softmax};
use crate::matvec_memo;
use crate::model::QType;
